  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">MRV system for mitigation actions in Indonesia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">With the aim of fulfilling the reporting obligations of the Paris Agreement, Indonesia is establishing a national MRV system for its measures to reduce greenhouse gas emissions. The project supported the government in developing the system by helping national and sub-national stakeholders to integrate the existing PEP tool into the new solution. It also helped the &#x2018;Secretariat of the National Action Plan on Mitigation&#x2019; to collect data and set up a data management system. The project strengthened the capacity building of national and sub-national partners regarding the reporting of mitigation measures, and also developed guidelines, regulations, training material and communication products, ensuring that the measures achieve a wide-ranging impact. The project was part of the IKI Corona Response Package. As part of the IKI Corona Response Package, the project advised the Indonesian government on sustainable economic incentives and green fiscal policies.</narrative>
  </description>
